=== Home Visit Considerations

When in-person assessment is essential (physical examination, procedures), home visits may be necessary. Considerations include:

    - *Advance notice*: 24–48 hours minimum so family can prepare and child can rest beforehand
    - *Minimal stimulation*: Visitors should speak quietly, minimize movements, avoid fragrances
    - *Examination in place*: Examine child in bed if unable to sit; avoid requiring position changes that trigger orthostatic symptoms
    - *Brief duration*: Complete essential examination in minimum time; defer non-urgent components
    - *Recovery time*: Expect child to need 1–3 days recovery from home visit; schedule accordingly

